Collapse this into:

try:
  self._print(self._queue.popleft())
except IndexError:
  time.sleep(0.1)

...or put the print in an else, and ditch the continue?

I prefer doing multiple imports this way:

from foo.bar import {
  baz,
  biz
}

At least I think it works that way. Makes diffs really easy to read.
